<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 4:28PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Hidalgo County through 515 PM CDT...
At 428 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
South McAllen, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mission, Pharr, San Juan, Alamo, Hidalgo, North McAllen, Sharyland,
South McAllen, Edinburg Regional Medical Center and Austin Middle
School.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
